Factor 1: Substantial 8-15. High risk of physical safety requiring the provision of community care services to prevent a breakdown in care. The user has a sensory impairment or will develop health problems such that care or living arrangements will break down or become unsafe without the provision of community care services. Accommodation presents a grossly hazardous environment indicating a need for community care services. Substantial risk to health and safety due to accommodation needs now or in the foreseeable future without the provision of community care services. Abuse or neglect has occurred, or will occur. Highly vulnerable to being a victim or perpetrator of physical or sexual abuse or neglect, emotional or psychological abuse without provision of community care services.